{
  "answer": "**The work is *San Hyan Tattvajnana* (Knowledge of Reality) by Unknown, a medieval Kawi prose text; the passage appears in Chapter 1 (its only chapter).**[^1]\n\nThis chapter maps the macrocosm of the universe onto the human microcosm (*aṇḍabhuvana*, the \"cosmic egg\" body), establishing the seven mountains (*Saptaparvvata*), seven oceans (*Saptārṇṇava*), and seven continents (*Saptadvīpa*) within the body.[^2]\n\nThe seven mountains are equated to specific organs as follows:[^3]\n* The kidneys are Mount Mālyavān.\n* The pelvic region is Mount Niṣedha.\n* The spleen is Mount Gandhamādana.\n* The lungs are Mount Malayamahīdhara.\n* The gall bladder is Mount Triśṛṅga.\n* The liver is Mount Vindhya.\n* The heart is Mount Mahāmeru.\n\n**The seven oceans are quoted verbatim:** \"The seven oceans (*Saptārṇṇava*) are as follows:  \n* Urine is the fresh water ocean.  \n* Blood is the ocean of sugarcane juice.  \n* Sweat is the salt ocean.  \n* Fat is the oil ocean.  \n* Saliva is the honey ocean.  \n* Marrow is the milk ocean.  \n* The brain is the ocean of curds.\"[^4]\n\n**The seven continents are quoted verbatim:** \"The seven continents (*Saptadvīpa*) are as follows:  \n* Bone is Jambudvīpa.  \n* Sinew is Kuśadvīpa.  \n* Flesh is Śaṅkhadvīpa.  \n* Skin is Śālmalidvīpa.  \n* The neck is Gomedhadvīpa.  \n* Bodily vapor is Puṣkaradvīpa.  \n* Teeth are Krauñcadvīpa.\"[^5]\n\n[^1]: *San Hyan Tattvajnana*, ch. 1, [/works/unknown-san-hyan-tattvajnana-1f29bd/01/translation/](/works/unknown-san-hyan-tattvajnana-1f29bd/01/translation/).\n\n[^2]: Ibid., [p-588c27](/works/unknown-san-hyan-tattvajnana-1f29bd/01/translation/#p-588c27).\n\n[^3]: Ibid., [p-786243](/works/unknown-san-hyan-tattvajnana-1f29bd/01/translation/#p-786243).\n\n[^4]: Ibid., [p-417b1b](/works/unknown-san-hyan-tattvajnana-1f29bd/01/translation/#p-417b1b).\n\n[^5]: Ibid., [p-09a726](/works/unknown-san-hyan-tattvajnana-1f29bd/01/translation/#p-09a726).",
